retrofit:HooksMainOnlyNoOp a retrofit:SPOF ;
    rdfs:label "pre-commit/pre-push hooks are main-only -- ACCEPTED, deliberate design" ;
    retrofit:standing "Accepted" ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:PullRequestPath ;
    retrofit:evidence "RE-CONFIRMED CURRENT 2026-07-21: scripts/hooks/pre-commit.sh lines 9-13 and pre-push.sh's equivalent both still silently exit 0 on any non-main branch. This is not undisclosed: CLAUDE.md's own 'Git Hooks & Build Gotchas' section documents this as deliberate ('deliberate, not a bug... feature-branch validation deferred to PR-time CI: ci.yml/quality.yml trigger on pull_request'), with the explicit consequence named ('a green git commit/git push on a feature branch carries no hook-provided guarantee -- just pre-commit/just check/just test must be run manually'). Bounded accepted risk: scope=local hook silence on feature branches only, failure consequence=a developer skipping manual just pre-commit before pushing (mitigated by real PR-time CI enforcement), owner=documented in CLAUDE.md, review trigger=if PR-time CI itself is ever found to have a gap this silence could hide." .

retrofit:ReleaseGateBrokenForWeeks a retrofit:SPOF ;
    rdfs:label "release.yml audit gate -- REPAIRED, CI-confirmation pending" ;
    retrofit:standing "Blocking" ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:ReleasePath ;
    retrofit:evidence "RESOLVED (root cause + fix), NOT YET CI-CONFIRMED, re-verified 2026-07-21: commit 53961f0ac / merged PR #349 identified the exact gate -- `cargo cicd status audit` hardcoded an OCEL evidence path but `wpm audit` only parses XES, so every release-workflow run refused with a format-mismatch error (confirmed against a real GH Actions run URL in that commit's own message). Live .github/workflows/release.yml now calls `wpm audit \"$XES\"` against the real events.xes sibling file, bypassing the OCEL-hardcoded path -- fix is committed and live. Kept Blocking, not restood Accepted, because that PR's own disclosed standing says a real green release.yml run post-fix is still required before this can claim Proven -- the fix is a workflow-file diff plus local reproduction, not that run. Next action: observe the next real release.yml execution; restand to Accepted only once a genuine green run is observed, not before." .

retrofit:BrokenJustSyncRecipes a retrofit:SPOF ;
    rdfs:label "just sync / just sync-dry recipes -- RESOLVED, original flags no longer exist" ;
    retrofit:standing "Accepted" ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:ReleasePath, retrofit:GenerationPath ;
